    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This project is part of the Learning from Gulf Cities initiative, promoted by Harvey Molotch and Davide Ponzini, and is the continuation of the long-term photographic research on spectacular architecture Nastasi started in 2008. A Gulf of Images creates a photographic survey of spectacular buildings and cityscapes in the most important cities of the Gulf, investigating the peculiar aspects of each city, and making comparison in-between different ones. The photographs delineate aspects that are common to all the cities - with a special attention to the spectacularization of urban landscapes - as well as differences and nuances.</field>
    <field name="bioghist_teim">Michele Nastasi is an architectural researcher and a photographer of architecture and cities. Since 2007 he has been a member of the editorial staff of the magazine Lotus international, and is a PhD Candidate in History of Arts at Ca' Foscari University of Venice/IUAV. His photographs has been published in international journals and books — Starchitecture: Scenes, Actors and Spectacles in Contemporary Cities, with Davide Ponzini; Suspended City: L'Aquila after the Earthquake; Shooting Space: Architecture in Contemporary Photography — and exhibited in numerous solo and group exhibitions in Italy and the United States. He has taught Photography of Architecture at the Politecnico di Milano.</field>
